{"cursor":"11334","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n{| class=\"infobox\" style=\"width: 21em; font-size: 90%; text-align: left\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | [[Godzilla film series]] character\n|- colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | -\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size: larger; background-color:\n! #001; color: #ffa;\" |Rodan\n|-\n! Species\n| Dai-Kaiju -\n! Sub Species\n| Giant pterosaur -\n! Alias\n| Radon Monster Zero-Two\n|-\n! Height\n| 50â100 meters -\n! Weight\n| 15,000-30,000 tons -\n! Wingspan\n| 120â200 meters -\n! Air speed\n| Mach 1.5-3.5 -\n! Faction\n| Earth Defenders -\n! Relationships\n| Baby Godzilla (Surrogate brother) -\n! Major Enemies\n| Godzilla (Heisei series and Millennium series) King\n| Ghidorah Mechagodzilla -\n! Allies\n| Godzilla Mothra Anguirus King\n| Caesar Gorosaurus Baragon Varan Manda Minilla -\n! Controlled by\n| Xiliens Kilaaks -\n! First appearance\n| [[Rodan (film)|Rodan]] -\n! Created by\n| Ken Kuronuma -\n! Portrayed by:\n| 'ShÅwa series' Haruo Nakajima KÅji Uruki Masaki Shinohara Teruo\n| Aragaki 'Millennium series' Naoko Kamio }\n\n is a fictional Japanese mutated pterosaur introduced in [[Rodan (film)|Rodan]],\n a 1956 release from Toho Studios, the company that produced the Godzilla\n series. Like Godzilla and Anguirus, he is designed after a type of prehistoric\n reptile (the Japanese name \"Radon\" is a contraction of\n \"pte'''ra'''no'''don'''\"). Radon is usually referred to as \"Rodan\" in the\n United States, possibly to avoid confusion with the atomic element Radon; any\n time his name is written in English in Japan, it is written as Rodan. He is\n occasionally portrayed as a rival and enemy of Godzilla, but is usually\n depicted as one of Godzilla's allies, much like Anguirus. Rodan and Anguirus\n both started out as enemies of Godzilla, which explains the occasional enmity\n between the creatures and Godzilla himself on the rare occasio